-- Dong Completes $790 Million Sale of Offshore Wind Stake
-- B y   M a r c   R o c a
-- 2012-05-25T14:58:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/dong-completes-790-million-sale-of-offshore-wind-stake.html
Dong Energy A/S completed the sale of
a 50 percent stake in its Borkum Riffgrund 1 offshore wind power
project in  Germany  to Kirkbi A/S, parent company of Lego Group,
and the Oticon Foundation.  The Danish utility finalized the 4.7 billion kroner ($790
million) transaction for the 277.2-megawatt project after
competition authorities approved the deal, it said today in a
statement. The sale was announced on Feb 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marc Roca in London at 
